##Short Explanation of Scraping Logic
This project uses Python and Selenium to automate a web browser and extract laptop data from product listing pages. 
The script opens the target website, waits for the page to load, and identifies product elements using HTML tags such as h2, h3, and elements containing the class name price.
The extracted laptop names and prices are stored in a structured format using a Pandas DataFrame. 
The price column is then cleaned by removing the ₹ symbol and commas, and converted into numeric format for analysis.
Finally, the combined dataset is exported as a CSV file, and various visualizations such as bar charts, histograms, 
box plots, and comparison charts are generated to analyze price distribution and market trends.
